## Scope

This packet documents the State Transportation Improvement Program
(STIP) programming entries for each candidate project produced by
ClawModeler run `{{ run_id }}`. California's STIP is governed by
Streets & Highways Code §§14525-14529.11 and the current CTC STIP
Guidelines; it is adopted biennially by the California Transportation
Commission and programs Regional Improvement Program (RIP, 75% share)
and Interregional Improvement Program (IIP, 25% share) funds across a
four-year horizon. S&HC §188 further requires a 40% northern region /
60% southern region statewide split.

## Methodology

Per the CTC STIP Guidelines, each candidate programmed into the cycle
must attach:

- **Phase** — PA&ED (Project Approval & Environmental Document), PS&E
  (Plans, Specifications & Estimate), R/W (Right-of-Way), or CON
  (Construction).
- **Fiscal year** — California's state fiscal year follows the format
  `YYYY-YY` (e.g., `2026-27` denotes July 2026 through June 2027).
- **Programmed cost** — in thousands of dollars, matching the CTC's
  application currency.
- **Funding source** — ``RIP`` (Regional Improvement Program), ``IIP``
  (Interregional Improvement Program), ``SB1``, or another
  CTC-recognized category.
- **PPNO** — the Caltrans Project Programming Number, assigned when
  the project enters a Caltrans districts' PPNO directory. Candidates
  that do not yet carry a PPNO are reported without one; the lead
  agency must coordinate with the district before the application
  package is assembled.
- **Region** — ``north`` (10-county northern region) or ``south``
  (12-county southern region) per S&HC §188.

ClawModeler does not synthesize STIP inputs. When the lead agency has
not yet staged the `stip_overlay.csv` sidecar (long format: one row
per project × phase × fiscal year), candidates are not represented in
the programming table; the portfolio count still reflects total
candidates.

